 traffic accident in US history.Unearthing a forgotten chapter in Chicago lore, The Green Hornet Streetcar Disaster tells the riveting tale of this calamity. Combing through newspaper accounts as well as the Chicago Transit Authority's official archives, Craig Cleve vividly brings to life this horrific catastrophe. Going beyond the historical record, he tracks down individuals who were present on that fateful day on State and 62nd: eyewitnesses, journalists, even survivors whose lives were forever changed by the accident. Weaving these sources together, Cleve reveals the remarkable combination of natural events, human error, and mechanical failure that led to the disaster, and this moving history recounts them—as well as the conflagration's human drama—in gripping detail.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDisasterszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aElectric railroad accidentszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aExplosionszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aGasolinexTransportationzIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aTraffic accidentszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aTraffic fatalitieszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aTruck accidentszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 4aMidwest. 4aTransportation. 4aU.S. History. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh  aState Street and 62nd Place, Chicago Transit Authority, streamlined streetcars, streetcar accident.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175775440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501757754423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501757754/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA